Thanks! If you want the entire sidebar to disappear (not just collapse to icons) when clicking the menu icon, follow these steps:


---

1. Update sidebar.component.ts

Keep a showSidebar boolean:

import { Component } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-sidebar',
  templateUrl: './sidebar.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./sidebar.component.css']
})
export class SidebarComponent {
  showSidebar = true;
  referenceDataExpanded = false;

  toggleSidebar() {
    this.showSidebar = !this.showSidebar;
  }

  toggleReferenceData() {
    this.referenceDataExpanded = !this.referenceDataExpanded;
  }
}


---

2. Update sidebar.component.html

Wrap the entire sidebar with *ngIf="showSidebar" so it completely disappears:

<button class="toggle-button" (click)="toggleSidebar()">
  <mat-icon>{{ showSidebar ? 'menu_open' : 'menu' }}</mat-icon>
</button>

<div *ngIf="showSidebar" class="sidebar-container">
  <ul class="menu">
    <li>
      <mat-icon>apartment</mat-icon>
      <span>Manage Company</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <mat-icon>description</mat-icon>
      <span>Recon Master</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <mat-icon>category</mat-icon>
      <span>Context Type</span>
    </li>

    <li (click)="toggleReferenceData()" class="expandable">
      <mat-icon>inventory_2</mat-icon>
      <span>Reference Data</span>
      <mat-icon>{{ referenceDataExpanded ? 'expand_less' : 'expand_more' }}</mat-icon>
    </li>

    <ul *ngIf="referenceDataExpanded" class="submenu">
      <li>Accounting Period Groups</li>
      <li>Calendars</li>
      <li>Counterparties</li>
      <li>Currencies</li>
      <li>Exchange Rates</li>
      <li>Item Types</li>
      <li>Reason Codes</li>
      <li>Securities</li>
      <li>Tags</li>
    </ul>

    <li>
      <mat-icon>search</mat-icon>
      <span>Audit</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <mat-icon>list_alt</mat-icon>
      <span>Logs</span>
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>


---

3. Basic CSS (sidebar.component.css)

.sidebar-container {
  width: 250px;
  background-color: #1b3b4b;
  color: white;
  height: 100vh;
  padding: 10px;
}

.toggle-button {
  background: none;
  border: none;
  color: #1b3b4b;
  margin: 10px;
  font-size: 24px;
  cursor: pointer;
}


---

Summary:

Menu icon always visible at top-left.

Sidebar fully disappears on toggle (not even icons shown).

You can adjust placement of the toggle button as needed.


Let me know if you want an animation or transition effect.

